tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Finished T114 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Three-time qualifier for U.S. Amateur Championship, becoming first Aggie in program history to earn the distinction...Tied tournament record at California State Fair Amateur Men's Championship in Sept. 2011, claiming medalist honors by one stroke...Became UC Davis men's golf program's first representative at the NCAA Div. I Championships in its short Div. I tenure in 20111...Big West Freshman of the Year in 2011...Won the Babe Slater Award in 2014, given to the Male Athlete of the Year at UC Davis...Helped lead UC Davis to the Big West title in 2014...Named PING All-Region in 2011 & 2014...Named PING All-American honorable mention in 2011 and Golfweek All-American honorable mention in 2014.
tourBios.personal: Attended Morro Bay High School in Moro Bay, Calif...Younger sister Megan plays basketball at Concordia University and was the county player of the year as a senior in high school...Favorite golf memory is breaking 70 for the first time. He found out later that the 67 he shot was a course record for juniors...Would like to be a golf coach, if he were not playing golf for a living...Not many people know that he named his golden retriever after Jack Nicklaus.

tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Finished fourth at the California Q-School, with rounds of 70-70-75-71...Made seven cuts in 11 starts on the Mackenzie Tour...Only top-25 performance came at the ATB Financial Classic...Carded four rounds in the 60s to finish T13.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA T was T13th in 2015 at the ATB Financial Classic.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks 44th in Scoring Average (Actual) on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA TOUR Canada.
